Practical–3.2: Exploring Multiple Activities
Aim To develop an Android application that demonstrates interaction between multiple activities by navigating between screens and presenting user-specific content dynamically.
Problem Statement Design an Android application consisting of two activities where the first activity acts as a welcome screen to collect basic user input, and the second activity displays a personalized message based on the input received, demonstrating activity-to-activity communication.

STEP 1: Create a New Android Project
              Open Android Studio
              •	Click New Project
              Select Template
              •	Choose Empty Views Activity
              •	Click Next
              Project Configuration 
              •	Name:
              WelcomeMessageApp
              •	Language:
              Java
              •	Minimum SDK:
              API 21 (Android 5.0)
              •	Build configuration language:
              Groovy (default)
              Click Finish
              Wait for Gradle sync to complete.
              
